3. SCALING LAW: ADVANTAGE AT EACH LEVEL vs p
======================================================================

  The disjointness excess at (k,k) pairs scales as:
  excess ~ p * b_k^2 * (m^2-1)/12
  where b_k = C(m-2, k-3) and m = (p-1)/2


  k=3:
